    <!-- Registration Process -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>How to Register</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            <p>Follow these steps to register for the NBT:</p>
            
            <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
                <div>
                    <h4>Step 1: Check University Requirements</h4>
                    <p>
                        Verify with your chosen university whether they require NBT results and which tests 
                        you need to write (AQL and/or MAT).
                    </p>
                </div>
                
                <div>
                    <h4>Step 2: Register Online</h4>
                    <p>
                        Complete the online registration form. You will need:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Valid South African ID number or passport number</li>
                        <li>Email address</li>
                        <li>Cellphone number</li>
                        <li>School information</li>
                        <li>Universities you're applying to</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h4>Step 3: Pay Registration Fee</h4>
                    <p>
                        Current fees (subject to change):
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>AQL Test:</strong> R140</li>
                        <li><strong>MAT Test:</strong> R140</li>
                        <li><strong>Both Tests (same sitting):</strong> R280</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Payment can be made via credit card, EFT, or at selected retail stores.</p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h4>Step 4: Select Test Date and Venue</h4>
                    <p>
                        Choose your preferred test date and venue from available options. 
                        Test venues are located throughout South Africa.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h4>Step 5: Receive Confirmation</h4>
                    <p>
                        You will receive a confirmation email with your test details and instructions 
                        on what to bring on test day.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </FluentStack>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Test Information -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Test Information</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            
            <FluentAccordion>
                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Academic and Quantitative Literacy (AQL)" Expanded="true">
                    <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="12">
                        <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 3 hours</p>
                        <p><strong>Format:</strong> Multiple choice questions</p>
                        <p><strong>Components:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Academic Literacy:</strong> Tests reading comprehension, reasoning, and 
                                language use in academic contexts</li>
                            <li><strong>Quantitative Literacy:</strong> Assesses ability to work with numbers, 
                                data, and spatial information in real-world contexts</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>What to bring:</strong> ID document, pen, pencil, eraser, non-programmable calculator</p>
                    </FluentStack>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Mathematics (MAT)">
                    <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="12">
                        <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 3 hours</p>
                        <p><strong>Format:</strong> Multiple choice questions</p>
                        <p><strong>Content areas:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Number and operations with numbers</li>
                            <li>Patterns, relationships, and functions</li>
                            <li>Space, shape, and measurement</li>
                            <li>Data handling and probability</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>What to bring:</strong> ID document, pen, pencil, eraser, non-programmable calculator</p>
                    </FluentStack>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Test Day Information">
                    <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="12">
                        <p><strong>What to bring:</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Original ID document or passport (certified copy not accepted)</li>
                            <li>Confirmation email or SMS</li>
                            <li>Black or blue pens</li>
                            <li>HB pencils and eraser</li>
                            <li>Non-programmable calculator</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Arrival time:</strong> Arrive at least 30 minutes before your scheduled test time</p>
                        <p><strong>Not allowed:</strong> Cellphones, smartwatches, programmable calculators, notes, or any electronic devices</p>
                    </FluentStack>
                </FluentAccordionItem>
            </FluentAccordion>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Results Information -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Understanding Your Results</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            <p>
                Your results will be sent directly to the universities you specified during registration. 
                Results are typically available within 4-6 weeks after writing.
            </p>
            
            <h4>Performance Bands</h4>
            <p>NBT results are reported in performance bands:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Proficient:</strong> Academic performance can be expected to be adequate</li>
                <li><strong>Intermediate:</strong> Challenges are predicted, which could be managed 
                    through access to special support</li>
                <li><strong>Basic:</strong> Serious learning challenges are predicted ‚Äì an extended 
                    curriculum program or foundation provision is recommended</li>
            </ul>

            <FluentMessageBar Intent="MessageIntent.Info">
                NBT results are valid for 3 years from the date of writing. You can write the tests 
                more than once, and universities will consider your best scores.
            </FluentMessageBar>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- Preparation Resources -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>How to Prepare</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            <p>
                While you cannot "study" for the NBTs in the traditional sense, you can prepare by:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Reviewing the sample tests available on this website</li>
                <li>Reading widely in English (newspapers, academic texts, novels)</li>
                <li>Practicing mathematical problem-solving</li>
                <li>Working with data, graphs, and tables</li>
                <li>Ensuring you understand basic mathematical concepts</li>
            </ul>
            <FluentButton Appearance="Appearance.Accent" Href="/resources">
                Access Practice Materials
            </FluentButton>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

    <!-- FAQs -->
    <FluentCard>
        <FluentStack Orientation="Orientation.Vertical" VerticalGap="16">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <FluentDivider />
            
            <FluentAccordion>
                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Do I have to write the NBT?">
                    <p>
                        It depends on your chosen university. Most South African universities require NBT 
                        results as part of their admissions process. Check with your university for their 
                        specific requirements.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="When should I write the NBT?">
                    <p>
                        It's recommended to write the NBT in Grade 12, preferably in the first half of the year. 
                        This ensures your results are available when you apply to universities.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="Can I write the tests more than once?">
                    <p>
                        Yes, you can write the NBT more than once. Universities will consider your best scores. 
                        However, you must wait at least 6 months before re-writing.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="What if I miss my test date?">
                    <p>
                        If you miss your scheduled test date, you will need to register and pay for a new 
                        test session. No refunds are given for missed tests.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>

                <FluentAccordionItem Heading="How do I send my results to universities?">
                    <p>
                        Results are automatically sent to the universities you specify during registration. 
                        If you need to send results to additional universities, you can request this online 
                        for a fee.
                    </p>
                </FluentAccordionItem>
            </FluentAccordion>
        </FluentStack>
    </FluentCard>

